BRIEFING:
A FRAGMENTED BAND OF LOW CLOUDS AND SHOWERS ASSOCIATED WITH A COLD FRONT WILL TRACK SE ACROSS THE ISLANDS TODAY, THEN STALL AND DISSIPATE NEAR THE BIG ISLAND LATE TONIGHT AND THURSDAY. PERIODS OF MVFR VIS/CIG CAN BE EXPECTED IN SHRA, WITH ISOL IFR VIS IN +SHRA AS THE BOUNDARY PASSES, WITH CLOUD TOPS POTENTIALLY AS HIGH AS 20 KFT. VFR CONDITIONS WILL PREVAIL OVER THE BIG ISLAND TODAY, WITH THE POTENTIAL FOR MVFR CIG/VIS POSSIBLE OVER LEEWARD BIG ISLAND BY TONIGHT.
THREAT: SIGMET YANKEE SERIES OVER KAUAI FOR FCST SEV TURB FL250/370 MOVING SOUTHEAST.
